download and install java 8 from:

https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#java8-windows

download "jdk-8u401-windows-x64.exe" from windows in Java SE Development Kit 8u401.

install by changing the installation location as:
install jre in c:\Java
install jdk in C:\Java\jsk-1.8
add JAVA_HOME=C:\Java\jsk-1.8 in environment variable
add C:\Java\jsk-1.8\bin in path

verify the installation in cmd using "java -version" keyword.
the output for valid installation is

java version "1.8.0_401"
Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_401-b10)
Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.401-b10, mixed mode)

download and extract hadoop-3.3.4 from:
https://archive.apache.org/dist/hadoop/common/hadoop-3.3.4/hadoop-3.3.4.tar.gz

extract the file at c:\hadoop-3.3.4
replace the bin,data and etc folder from the bin,etc,data.rar in the rar file from above.

type hdfs namenode -format in cmd at c:/hadoop-3.3.4/bin

type start-all.cmd in cmd at c:/hadoop-3.3.4/sbin

check if the hadoop is running or not by typing localhost:8088 and localhost:9870 in browser
